cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the concept of compensating users for their data in a human-centric data economy, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of recommender systems (cs.IR) and cooperative game theory (cs.GT) to determine fair compensation for users. Additionally, the paper touches on clustering and dimensionality reduction techniques (cs.SI) and partial information (cs.CE) to derive faster alternatives for determining the Shapley value.
